At least 32 Eastern Cape teachers are being investigated. The provincial education department says irregularities were picked up during the marking of the Life Sciences, Physical Science and Accounting exam papers. Mbasa Khwaza has more. Courtesy #DStv403 MTHATHA - At least 32 Eastern Cape teachers have been implicated in alleged matric exam cheating. It’s believed the teachers were aware that some Grade 12 pupils were cheating during their final exams last year. The provincial education department is investigating the matter. READ: 2021 Matric Results | Motshekga: Best results in history of NSC The department said irregularities were picked up during the marking of the Life Sciences, Physical Science and Accounting exam papers. The Congress Of South African Students is calling for a thorough investigation. * Mbasa Khwaza reports.